      "Do not spend another branch on a plain H16/H32 source-boundary dKV producer unless it also fuses the cross-head merge on-chip.",
      "Keep full-H64 dKV contribution reduction as the target boundary for the compact page.",
      "If the first runtime prototype uses multiple CTAs, treat the HBM page as an explicit measured cost and require full source-boundary S4096 latency to beat 11.13 ms before e2e TFLOPs work.",
      "MORI/SHMEM is not a substitute for workgroup LDS here; it can help EP/MoE communication overlap, not share score pages between sibling CTAs inside one sparse-attention kernel."
    ]
